                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": ". Using DNA origami we constructed an autonomous DNA robot programmed to transport payloads and present them specifically in tumors. Our nanorobot is functionalized on the outside with a DNA aptamer that binds nucleolin, a protein specifically expressed on tumor-associated endothelial cells",
                  "bbox": [
                    38,
