                    392
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": ", ultimately leading to obstructive thrombosis. Naked thrombin is short-lived in the circulation and induces coagulation events indiscriminately, and has not been used in cancer treatment. For therapeutic use, it is therefore critical to precisely deliver thrombin solely to tumor sites in a highly controlled manner to minimize its effects in healthy tissues.",
                  "bbox": [
