                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "page_idx": 0,
              "bbox": [
                298,
                391,
                553,
                501
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "DNA origami is a method that enables the rational design and production of DNA nanostructures with controlled size, shape and spatial addressability[15-18], producing functional platforms for biological applications[3,4,6,19-22]. Using DNA origami, we constructed a DNA nanorobotic system to overcome the challenges associated with thrombin delivery to tumors. Our nanorobot protects thrombin until exposure is triggered by the interaction with the tumor vessel marker nucleolin. Using the thrombin-loaded nanorobot, we demonstrate on-site tumor blood vessel infarction and targeted cancer treatment in vivo.",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
                594,
                783
              ],
              "spans": [
                {
                  "text": "DNA origami is a method that enables the rational design and production of DNA nanostructures with controlled size, shape and spatial addressability[15-18], producing functional platforms for biological applications[3,4,6,19-22]. Using DNA origami, we constructed a DNA nanorobotic system to overcome the challenges associated with thrombin delivery to tumors. Our nanorobot protects thrombin until exposure is triggered by the interaction with the tumor vessel marker nucleolin. Using the thrombin-loaded nanorobot, we demonstrate on-site tumor blood vessel infarction and targeted cancer treatment in vivo.",
                  "bbox": [
