              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To deliver active thrombin solely to tumor sites in a highly controlled way, we developed a DNA nanorobotic system based on a self-assembled origami nanotube with multiple functional elements (Fig. 1a and Supplementary Table 1). A rectangular DNA origami sheet, measuring 90\\mathrm{nm} \\times 60\\mathrm{nm} \\times 2\\mathrm{nm} (Supplementary Fig. 1), was first prepared by assembling an M13 bacteriophage genome DNA strand and multiple staple strands. For thrombin loading, capture strands with poly-A sequences were extended at four designated locations on the surface of each DNA origami sheet (Supplementary Figs. 2 and 3). We synthesized the thrombin-DNA conjugates by attaching thiolated poly-T oligonucleotides to thrombin molecules through a",
