              "type": "text",
              "text": "We also examined the time-dependent organ distribution and clearance of the DNA nanorobots and controls after intravenous injection (Supplementary Fig. 22c). Shortly (1\\mathrm{h}) after injection, the DNA nanostructures accumulated in the liver, presumably having been captured by the mononuclear phagocyte system. In time, the intensity of the liver fluorescence decreased, suggesting that the nanostructures not entrapped by the tumor may be degraded following phagocytosis, as generally observed for nanoscale delivery vehicles[25]. At 24\\mathrm{h} post-injection, little fluorescence was observable in the major organs and the fluorescence in the tumor also decreased substantially demonstrating the successful clearance or degradation of the material.",
