            {
              "page_idx": 7,
              "bbox": [
                39,
                239,
                292,
                429
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "DNA origami design details. Production of M13 bacteriophage single-stranded DNA was according to Douglas et al.'s methods[33]. In detail, JM109 Escherichia coli were cultured overnight in LB medium, 5\\mathrm{ml} were diluted in 2\\times \\mathrm{YT} medium with 5\\mathrm{mM}\\mathrm{MgCl}_2 and placed in a 37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} shaker. When the optical density (OD 600) reached 0.5, p7249 M13 phages were mixed with the bacteria, and the culture incubated in a 37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} shaker. After a 5\\mathrm{h} incubation, the culture was collected and centrifuged at 6,000g for 30\\mathrm{min} to remove the bacteria pellets. NaCl (30\\mathrm{g / l}) and PEG (40\\mathrm{g / l}) were added to the supernatant containing phages and the mixture was incubated on ice for 1\\mathrm{h}. After 30\\mathrm{min} centrifugation at 10,000g, the phage pellet was collected and suspended in Tris-Cl (10\\mathrm{mM},\\mathrm{pH}8.5). After adding 0.2\\mathrm{MNaOH} and 1\\% SDS, the phage solution was mixed and incubated at 25^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} for 3\\mathrm{min}. After the addition of potassium acetate (3\\mathrm{M},\\mathrm{pH}5.5) for neutralization, the solution was incubated on ice for 10\\mathrm{min} and centrifuged (12,000g,30\\mathrm{min}). The ssDNA (7249\\mathrm{nt}) containing supernatant was collected and precipitated in ethanol (70\\%) on ice for 2\\mathrm{h}. After centrifuging at 12,000g for 30\\mathrm{min}, the DNA pellet was collected and washed in ethanol (70\\%) and then resuspended in Tris-Cl (10\\mathrm{mM},\\mathrm{pH}8.5). The concentrations of ssDNA were determined by UV-Vis spectrometry (Shimadzu Corp. Kyoto, Japan).",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
                594,
                783
              ],
