              "type": "text",
              "text": "The resulting rectangular DNA origami sheets were separated from excess staple strands using Amicon Ultra-0.5 ml 100 kD centrifugal filters (Millipore Corporation, Bedford, USA). The initial filtration was performed by adding 350\\mu \\mathrm{l}1\\times TAE-Mg buffer to 100\\mu \\mathrm{l} DNA sheets, and centrifuging for 3 min at 2,075g. Then two wash steps were performed by adding 350\\mu \\mathrm{l}1\\times TAE-Mg buffer and centrifuging for 3 min each at 2,075g. The remaining solution was collected and characterized using 1\\% agarose gel electrophoresis and atomic force microscopy (AFM).",
