              "type": "text",
              "text": "Preparation of thrombin-DNA conjugates and thrombin activity analysis. Thrombin-DNA conjugates were prepared using sulfosuccinimidyl-4-(N-maleimidomethyl) cyclohexane-1-carboxylate (sulfo-SMCC, Sigma-Aldrich,",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
                594,
                783
              ],
              "spans": [
                {
                  "text": "Preparation of thrombin-DNA conjugates and thrombin activity analysis. Thrombin-DNA conjugates were prepared using sulfosuccinimidyl-4-(N-maleimidomethyl) cyclohexane-1-carboxylate (sulfo-SMCC, Sigma-Aldrich,",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    700,
                    292,
                    732
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "page_idx": 7,
              "bbox": [
                298,
                59,
                553,
                180
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "St. Louis, MO) as a bifunctional cross-linker between thrombin and DNA. In a typical synthesis, 200\\mu \\mathrm{l}3\\mu \\mathrm{M} thrombin (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO, catalog No. T4648) was mixed with 9\\mu \\mathrm{l}15\\mathrm{mM} sulfo-SMCC at room temperature for 1\\textrm{h}. Excess sulfo-SMCC was removed using an Amicon Ultra-0.5 ml 30\\mathrm{kD} centrifugal filter and washing three times by centrifugation. The initial washing was conducted by adding 250\\mu \\mathrm{l} PBS to 200\\mu \\mathrm{l} of the mixture of sulfo-SMCC and thrombin, and centrifuging for 3\\mathrm{min} at 5,534g. The subsequent two washing steps were performed by adding 350\\mu \\mathrm{l} PBS and centrifuging for 3\\mathrm{min} at 5,534g. The residual solution was collected and a 15-fold excess of thiolated poly-T DNA was added. The mixture was incubated at 4^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} overnight and the final thrombin-DNA conjugates were purified using 30\\mathrm{kD} centrifugal filters. Conjugation was verified by 4 - 12\\% SDS-PAGE.",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
                594,
                783
              ],
              "spans": [
                {
                  "text": "St. Louis, MO) as a bifunctional cross-linker between thrombin and DNA. In a typical synthesis, ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    59,
                    553,
                    180
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "200\\mu \\mathrm{l}3\\mu \\mathrm{M}",
