              "bbox": [
                299,
                550,
                553,
                650
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "DNA nanorobot preparation for in vitro and in vivo imaging. Thrombin-loaded rectangular DNA nanostructures with imaging strands were mixed with fluorescent-dye-conjugated DNA in 1 \\times TAE-Mg buffer. The molar ratio of dye-modified DNA to each imaging strand was 3:1. The mixtures were heated to 45^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}, then cooled to 25^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} at a steady rate of 10\\mathrm{min} / {}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} using an Eppendorf Mastercycler. Excess dye-modified DNA was removed using 100\\mathrm{kD} centrifugal filters. A 20-fold molar excess of fasteners and a fivefold molar excess of targeting strands, including the AS1411 sequence, were subsequently added. The mixture was heated to 37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}, then cooled to 15^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} at a rate of 10\\mathrm{min} / {}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} to promote assembly.",
