              "type": "text",
              "text": "penicillin and 100\\mathrm{U / ml} streptomycin. The murine melanoma cell line B16-F10 was grown in RPMI 1640 medium supplemented with 10\\% FBS, 1\\% penicillin and streptomycin. Mouse brain endothelial cells (bEnd.3) were maintained in high-glucose DMEM supplemented with 10\\% FBS, 100\\mathrm{U / ml} penicillin and 100\\mathrm{U / ml} streptomycin. Cell line authentication was performed by short tandem repeat DNA profiling and comparison with a reference database. The cells were cultured at 37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}, 5\\% \\mathrm{CO}_{2} and were routinely tested for mycoplasma contamination.",
