            },
            {
              "page_idx": 8,
              "bbox": [
                39,
                150,
                292,
                241
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Cell surface expression of nucleolin. The expression of nucleolin on the cell surface was assessed with antibodies specific to human nucleolin using a Beckman Coulter CyAn ADP flow cytometer (Fullerton, CA, USA). HUVECs were trypsinized, washed twice in PBS, resuspended in 10\\% goat serum in PBS, and incubated at 4^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} for 30\\mathrm{min}. Cells were then pelleted and resuspended in 2\\% goat serum in PBS containing 20~\\mu \\mathrm{g / ml} anti-nucleolin antibody. After 1\\textrm{h} incubation on ice, cells were washed three times with PBS and incubated with a 1:500 dilution of FITC-conjugated goat anti-rabbit IgG in PBS for 30\\mathrm{min} on ice. Cells were washed with PBS twice and analyzed by flow cytometry.",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
