              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Cell surface binding of AS1411 aptamer-containing DNA strands. HUVECs were prepared and blocked with goat serum. FITC-labeled F50-containing the AS1411 aptamer sequence (5'- FITC-GGTGGTGGTTGTGGTGG TGGTGG TCTAAAGTTTGTCGTGAATTGCG -3', the region of AS1411 aptamer is in bold font) that can recognize nucleolin on the surface of HUVECs was used. Cells were incubated with 2\\mu \\mathrm{M} FITC-labeled F50 strands (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) or 2\\mu \\mathrm{M} random DNA sequence (5'-GAGAACCT GAGTCAGTATTGCGGAGATCTAAAGTTTTGTCGTGAATTGCG -3') as a control for 2\\mathrm{h} at 37^{\\circ}C. Cells were washed twice with PBS and assayed by flow cytometry using a BD Biosciences BD Accuri C6 flow cytometer (San Jose, CA, USA).",
              "line_count": 1,
