                129,
                292,
                291
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In vivo thrombotic risk assessment in Bama miniature pigs. To evaluate the in vivo safety of DNA nanorobot-Th, Bama minipigs were randomly divided into three groups of three pigs per treatment group as follows: group 1, saline; group 2, free thrombin at a dose of 150\\mathrm{U} thrombin/pig (equivalent to \\sim 1.5\\mathrm{U} accumulated thrombin/mouse); group 3, nanorobot-Th. The animals were injected via marginal ear vein every other day for a total of three injections. Day 0 marks the first day of injection. Blood was collected from the marginal ear vein into sodium citrate (3.8% flonal concentration) at different time points (0 h, 2 h, 24 h, 3 d and 5 d) and immediately sent to the Clinical Laboratory, Changping hospital, Beijing, China, for measurements of coagulation parameters. At this institute, normal values for these parameters are as followings: PT: 11.5-15 s; APTT: 28-43 s; TT: 13-21 s; Fibrinogen: 2-4 g/l; D-dimer: 0 - 0.5\\mu \\mathrm{g / ml}. The animals were killed 3 d after the last treatment and the major organs were excised and stained with H&E for histological examination. The following formula was used to perform dose conversion between mice and pigs:",
