            {
              "page_idx": 9,
              "bbox": [
                39,
                180,
                292,
                230
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "HUVECs were prepared and blocked with goat serum as described above. Serum-starved HUVECs where surface nucleolin expression was downregulated were also used. Non-starved and serum-starved cells were incubated with DNA nanorobots labeled with fluorophore-quencher fasteners for 2\\mathrm{h} at 37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}. Cells were washed twice with PBS and assayed using flow cytometry.",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
                594,
                783
              ],
              "spans": [
                {
                  "text": "HUVECs were prepared and blocked with goat serum as described above. Serum-starved HUVECs where surface nucleolin expression was downregulated were also used. Non-starved and serum-starved cells were incubated with DNA nanorobots labeled with fluorophore-quencher fasteners for ",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    180,
                    292,
                    230
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "2\\mathrm{h}",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    180,
                    292,
                    230
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " at ",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    180,
                    292,
                    230
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    180,
                    292,
                    230
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": ". Cells were washed twice with PBS and assayed using flow cytometry.",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    180,
                    292,
                    230
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "page_idx": 9,
              "bbox": [
                39,
                239,
                292,
                360
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Cell binding of nanorobot. HUVECs were trypsinized, washed twice with 1\\mathrm{ml} PBS, seeded onto Lab-Tek Chamber Slides (Nunc) and cultured overnight. Cells were then incubated with either 15~\\mu \\mathrm{M} Alexa 594-labeled AS1411 aptamer or Alexa 594-labeled nanorobots or nanotubes at a concentration equivalent to 15~\\mu \\mathrm{M} F50 at 37^{\\circ}C for different time periods. To determine whether binding of the nanorobot was dependent on surface nucleolin, the cells were pretreated with anti-nucleolin antibodies (45~\\mu \\mathrm{g / ml}). After treatment, the cells were washed three times with PBS and fixed with 4 \\% paraformaldehyde for 30\\mathrm{min}. Then the cells were stained with DIO (plasma membrane) and DAPI (nucleus) (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO) and imaged with a Nikon Ti-e microscope equipped with an UltraVIEW Vox confocal attachment (Perkin Elmer, Boston, MA, USA).",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
                594,
                783
              ],
              "spans": [
                {
                  "text": "Cell binding of nanorobot. HUVECs were trypsinized, washed twice with ",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    239,
                    292,
                    360
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "1\\mathrm{ml}",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    239,
                    292,
                    360
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " PBS, seeded onto Lab-Tek Chamber Slides (Nunc) and cultured overnight. Cells were then incubated with either ",
                  "bbox": [
                    39,
                    239,
                    292,
                    360
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
