              "bbox": [
                298,
                270,
                553,
                339
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Two other tumor models, an ovarian cancer SK-OV3 xenograft model and an inducible Kras^{G12D} lung tumor model were used to investigate the versatility of nanorobot-Th. For the SK-OV3 model, nude mice bearing \\sim 100~\\mathrm{mm}^3 SK-OV3 xenografts (eight mice per group) were treated intravenously with saline, free thrombin, empty nanorobot, a scrambled aptamer control, nontargeted nanotube-Th, targeted nanotube-Th or nanorobot-Th every 3\\mathrm{d} for a total of 6 treatments (\\sim 1.5\\mathrm{U} accumulated thrombin/mouse).",
              "line_count": 1,
