              "type": "text",
              "text": "Cell binding of nanorobot. HUVECs were trypsinized, washed twice with 1\\mathrm{ml} PBS, seeded onto Lab-Tek Chamber Slides (Nunc) and cultured overnight. Cells were then incubated with either 15~\\mu \\mathrm{M} Alexa 594-labeled AS1411 aptamer or Alexa 594-labeled nanorobots or nanotubes at a concentration equivalent to 15~\\mu \\mathrm{M} F50 at 37^{\\circ}C for different time periods. To determine whether binding of the nanorobot was dependent on surface nucleolin, the cells were pretreated with anti-nucleolin antibodies (45~\\mu \\mathrm{g / ml}). After treatment, the cells were washed three times with PBS and fixed with 4 \\% paraformaldehyde for 30\\mathrm{min}. Then the cells were stained with DIO (plasma membrane) and DAPI (nucleus) (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO) and imaged with a Nikon Ti-e microscope equipped with an UltraVIEW Vox confocal attachment (Perkin Elmer, Boston, MA, USA).",
