            {
              "page_idx": 8,
              "bbox": [
                299,
                260,
                552,
                301
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "HUVECs were prepared and blocked with goat serum as detailed above. Cells were then incubated with the Y-shaped DNA structures (F50 + C15, F50 + C26 and FC + CC) at a concentration of 2\\mu \\mathrm{M} for 2\\mathrm{h} at 37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}. Cells were washed twice with PBS and assayed using flow cytometry.",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
                594,
                783
              ],
              "spans": [
                {
                  "text": "HUVECs were prepared and blocked with goat serum as detailed above. Cells were then incubated with the Y-shaped DNA structures (F50 + C15, F50 + C26 and FC + CC) at a concentration of ",
                  "bbox": [
                    299,
                    260,
                    552,
                    301
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "2\\mu \\mathrm{M}",
                  "bbox": [
                    299,
                    260,
                    552,
                    301
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " for ",
                  "bbox": [
                    299,
                    260,
                    552,
                    301
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "2\\mathrm{h}",
                  "bbox": [
                    299,
                    260,
                    552,
                    301
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " at ",
                  "bbox": [
                    299,
                    260,
                    552,
                    301
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}",
                  "bbox": [
                    299,
                    260,
                    552,
                    301
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": ". Cells were washed twice with PBS and assayed using flow cytometry.",
                  "bbox": [
                    299,
                    260,
                    552,
                    301
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "page_idx": 8,
              "bbox": [
                298,
                310,
                553,
                429
              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "DNA nanorobot opening by recombinant nucleolin. We designed six pairs of fasteners consisting of 5^{\\prime}-FITC-labeled F50 and 3^{\\prime}-BHQ1-labeled Comp15: FITC-F50-48, Comp15-48-Q; FITC-F50-73, Comp15-73-Q; FITC-F50-97, Comp15-97-Q; FITC-F50-120, Comp15-120-Q; FITC-F50-144, Comp15-144-Q; and FITC-F50-169, Comp15-169-Q. The fluorophore-quencher pairs served as switchable fluorescent beacons. 20~\\mu \\mathrm{M} mixtures of fluorophore-quencher pairs in 1\\times TAE/Mg buffer were heated to 95^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} and then annealed by cooling to 25^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} at a rate of 3\\mathrm{min} / {}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} using an Eppendorf thermal cycler. A 20-fold molar excess of fluorophore-quencher fasteners was added to the DNA sheets. The mixture was heated to 37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}, then cooled to 15^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} at a rate of 10\\mathrm{min} / {}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} to promote assembly. Extra fastened pairs were removed using filtration devices.",
              "line_count": 1,
              "page_size": [
                594,
                783
              ],
              "spans": [
                {
                  "text": "DNA nanorobot opening by recombinant nucleolin. We designed six pairs of fasteners consisting of ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "5^{\\prime}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": "-FITC-labeled F50 and ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "3^{\\prime}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": "-BHQ1-labeled Comp15: FITC-F50-48, Comp15-48-Q; FITC-F50-73, Comp15-73-Q; FITC-F50-97, Comp15-97-Q; FITC-F50-120, Comp15-120-Q; FITC-F50-144, Comp15-144-Q; and FITC-F50-169, Comp15-169-Q. The fluorophore-quencher pairs served as switchable fluorescent beacons. ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "20~\\mu \\mathrm{M}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " mixtures of fluorophore-quencher pairs in ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "1\\times",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " TAE/Mg buffer were heated to ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "95^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " and then annealed by cooling to ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "25^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " at a rate of ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "3\\mathrm{min} / {}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " using an Eppendorf thermal cycler. A 20-fold molar excess of fluorophore-quencher fasteners was added to the DNA sheets. The mixture was heated to ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": ", then cooled to ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "15^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " at a rate of ",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "10\\mathrm{min} / {}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}",
                  "bbox": [
                    298,
                    310,
                    553,
                    429
                  ],
                  "type": "inline_equation"
                },
                {
                  "text": " to promote assembly. Extra fastened pairs were removed using filtration devices.",
                  "bbox": [
