              "type": "text",
              "text": "Cell surface nucleolin triggering of DNA nanorobot reconfiguration. 20\\mu \\mathrm{M} mixtures of FRET pairs in 1\\times TAE/Mg buffer were heated to 95^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} and then annealed by cooling to 25^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} at a rate of 3\\mathrm{min} / {}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} using an Eppendorf thermal cycler. A 20-fold molar excess of FRET fasteners was added to the DNA sheets. The mixture was heated to 37^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}, then cooled to 15^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} at a rate of 10\\mathrm{min} / {}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C} to promote assembly.",
