              ],
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Determination of platelet surface P-selectin, plasma fibrin and thrombin levels and platelet counts. Nude mice bearing MDA-MB-231 tumors were injected intravenously with DNA nanorobot-Th every 2 d for a total of six injections. Mouse whole blood was then collected retro-orbitally into a 3.8\\% sodium citrate solution in blood collection tubes at the indicated time points. For platelet activity studies, the blood was mixed with an equal volume of 2\\% paraformaldehyde for 30\\mathrm{min} at RT and centrifuged to obtain platelet-rich plasma (PRP). The PRP was incubated with FITC-conjugated P-selectin-specific monoclonal antibodies and analyzed by flow cytometry. Fibrin or thrombin levels in the PRP were quantified by enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) kits (Abcam, ab108844 and ab157527, respectively). Platelet numbers were counted manually with a hemocytometer using optical microscopy.",
              "line_count": 1,
